# Import an SSL Certificate into Spacewalk

Procedure for replacing the self-signed Spacewalk certificate with a CA-signed wildcard certificate: backing up the existing PKI material, staging the new cert and CA bundle, generating and installing the key-pair and trusted-cert RPMs, updating the jabberd certificate, and configuring the SMTP relay.

> Hostnames, paths, domain names, cert filenames, and email addresses below are generic placeholders.

## 1. Back up existing directories

```bash
mkdir ssl-bak
cd ssl-bak/
cp -prv /etc/httpd/conf                              httpd-conf-bak
cp -p   /etc/pki/spacewalk/jabberd/server.pem        pki-jabber-server.pem
cp -prv /root/ssl-build                              ssl-build-bak
cp -prv /var/www/html/pub                            html-pub
ls
```

## 2. Stage the domain certificate and CA bundle

Copy the wildcard domain certificate into the server build directory:

```bash
cd /home/opsadmin/certs/
ls
cp /home/opsadmin/certs/star_example_net.crt /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/server.crt
```

Copy the CA certificate bundle to the trusted-cert path:

```bash
cp /home/opsadmin/certs/star_example_net.ca-bundle /root/ssl-build/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT
```

Verify the domain certificate against the CA public certificate:

```bash
openssl verify -CAfile /root/ssl-build/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/server.crt
```

## 3. Store the CA certificate in the Spacewalk DB

```bash
rhn-ssl-dbstore -v --ca-cert=/root/ssl-build/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT
```

## 4. Generate and install the web server SSL package

```console
# rhn-ssl-tool --gen-server --rpm-only --dir /root/ssl-build
...working...

Generating web server's SSL key pair/set RPM:
    /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/rhn-org-httpd-ssl-key-pair-spacewalk01-1.0-2.src.rpm
    /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/rhn-org-httpd-ssl-key-pair-spacewalk01-1.0-2.noarch.rpm

Generating the web server's SSL key set and CA SSL public certificate archive:
    /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/rhn-org-httpd-ssl-archive-spacewalk01-1.0-2.tar

Deploy the server's SSL key pair/set RPM:
    The "noarch" RPM needs to be deployed to the machine working as a
    web server, or Red Hat Satellite, or Spacewalk Proxy.
    Presumably 'spacewalk01.example.net'.
```

Install the key-pair RPM:

```console
# rpm -Uhv /root/ssl-build/spacewalk01/rhn-org-httpd-ssl-key-pair-spacewalk01-1.0-2.noarch.rpm
Preparing...                ########################################### [100%]
   1:rhn-org-httpd-ssl-key-p########################################### [100%]
```

## 5. Generate and install the public CA certificate package

```console
# rhn-ssl-tool --gen-ca --dir=/root/ssl-build --rpm-only
...working...
Generating CA public certificate RPM:
    /root/ssl-build/rhn-org-trusted-ssl-cert-1.0-2.src.rpm
    /root/ssl-build/rhn-org-trusted-ssl-cert-1.0-2.noarch.rpm
```

Install the generated RPM (if the Spacewalk server is registered as a Spacewalk client):

```console
# rpm -Uvh /root/ssl-build/rhn-org-trusted-ssl-cert-1.0-2.noarch.rpm
Preparing...                ########################################### [100%]
   1:rhn-org-trusted-ssl-cer########################################### [100%]
update-ca-trust: Warning: The dynamic CA configuration feature is in the disabled state
```

Publish the RPM and raw CA certificate under `/var/www/html/pub`:

```bash
cp /root/ssl-build/rhn-org-trusted-ssl-cert-1.0-2.noarch.rpm /var/www/html/pub/
cp /root/ssl-build/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT                   /var/www/html/pub
```

Verify the published cert matches the source with a checksum:

```bash
sha1sum /root/ssl-build/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT \
        /usr/share/rhn/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT \
        /var/www/html/pub/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT
```

## 6. Update the jabberd certificate

Stop the service and clear any stale jabberd DB files:

```bash
spacewalk-service stop
rm -Rf /var/lib/jabberd/db/*
```

Back up the TLS directory and install the domain private key:

```bash
cp -rv /etc/pki/tls /home/opsadmin/ssl-bak/pki-tls-bak
cp /home/opsadmin/certs/star_example_net.key /etc/pki/tls/private/spacewalk.key
```

Back up the jabberd cert, then rebuild it from the domain certificate and key:

```bash
cp /etc/pki/spacewalk/jabberd/server.pem /home/opsadmin/ssl-bak/pki-jabber-server.pem_2

cd /home/opsadmin/certs
cat /home/opsadmin/certs/star_example_net.crt  > /etc/pki/spacewalk/jabberd/server.pem
cat /home/opsadmin/certs/star_example_net.key >> /etc/pki/spacewalk/jabberd/server.pem
```

> **Note:** the same result can be achieved by editing the file directly — `/etc/pki/spacewalk/jabberd/server.pem` should contain only the domain certificate and key.

Start the service and watch the log to troubleshoot:

```bash
spacewalk-service start
tail -f /var/log/messages
```

## 7. Configure the SMTP relay and sender address

```bash
vim /etc/rhn/rhn.conf
```

```ini
# Settings for SMTP relay host and sender address
web.smtp_server=<mail_server_hostname>
web.default_mail_from=ops@example.com
```

```bash
spacewalk-service restart
```